3.1 Webstore Content
3.2 Webstore design
3.2.1 As to the customers request the design of the web siteshould be basic, clean, and more personal.
3.2.2 He would like it to include a blog type forum where theaudience, fans, and followers can post pictures and comments.
3.2.3 The web store should have pictures for each article ofclothing, with a detailed close up to show the quality and tags.
	3.3  Webstore construction
3 .4 Webstore testing
3.4.1 Testing can beconducted by preforming the regular actions of a potential customer. A testersshould go to the web store and proceed through the checkout after selecting thedesired items. Tester should make sure all the functionalities available to theuser are in working order.

4.0 Monitoring and Controlling
4.1 Weekly Meetings
5.0 Assumptions
5.1 Payment in web store will either be taken care of through Big Cartel or done within the web store itself. Responsibilities of marketing for the site will be  handled elsewhere. We should be provided with a design architecture for the aesthetic feel of the site.
6.0 Constraints
6.1 We have limited time to implement a web store for a up and coming clothing line.
6.2 Our team is given limited resources toconstruct a project of this magnitude.
 	6.3 Our knowledge about clothing line web stores may be limited.
